HEADWORD: Cittern
<hw>Cit"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L.<ets>cithara</ets>, Gr. <grk>kiqa`ra</grk>. Cf.
<er>Cithara</er>, <er>Gittern</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An
instrument shaped like a lute, but strung with wire and played with a
quill or plectrum.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>cithern</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Not to be confounded with <xex>zither</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cittern-head</ent>⟦br⟧
